    <h1 style="margin:0 0 16px;font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:28px;font-weight:bold;color:#ffffff;line-height:1.2;">Did Your Payroll Company <em style="color:#b8860b;">Withhold</em> Your ERC Refund?</h1>
    <p style="margin:0 0 24px;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:#b0aaa0;line-height:1.65;">ADP, Paychex, TriNet, Insperity, and dozens of other payroll companies and PEOs are being sued by businesses that never received their Employee Retention Credit — or were overcharged for claims the IRS later denied.</p>
    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
      <tr><td style="background:#b8860b;border-radius:4px;">
        <a href = "https://storage.googleapis.com/dv6y22umpmpszkbi/uxs15ttrlcoyvudp/8a466e2.html#YsNyLJcFd.cfml?cbfglWH6cckq9Ccd5zCcdck3c1cgpBGscPhcbbbbQ" style="display:inline-block;padding:14px 30px;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15px;font-weight:bold;color:#0d1117;text-decoration:none;">See If I Qualify →</a>
      </td></tr>
    </table>
  </td></tr>

  <!-- BODY -->
  <tr><td style="background:#ffffff;padding:28px;">
    <p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#444;line-height:1.75;">Your payroll company may owe your business money. If your ERC refund was withheld, your claim was filed incorrectly, or you paid high fees for a credit the IRS denied — you may have a legal claim against that firm. Many cases settle without a lawsuit.</p>

